VALUES
(43, 3, 6, 48, 5, 16, 21, 'that which is born of the flesh is flesh', 'Flesh vs. Spirit Contrast', 'Both passages emphasize the conflict between the flesh and the Spirit. John 3:6 introduces the distinction, while Galatians 5:16-21 elaborates on the consequences of living according to each nature.', 'theme', 0.482, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 6, 26, 36, 26, 27, 'that which is born of the Spirit', 'Connection of Spirit and Heart', 'Both passages emphasize the transformation of the inner self. John speaks of being born of the Spirit, while Ezekiel describes receiving a new spirit and heart. This connection highlights the theme of spiritual renewal.', 'theme', 0.44699999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 6, 45, 8, 4, 9, 'that which is born of the Spirit', 'Connection of Flesh and Spirit', 'Both passages emphasize the distinction between the flesh and the Spirit. John 3:6 introduces the concept of being born of the Spirit, which Romans 8:4-9 elaborates on by contrasting those who walk after the flesh with those who walk after the Spirit.', 'theme', 0.43299999999999994, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 6, 47, 5, 17, 17, 'that which is born of the Spirit is spirit', 'New Birth and Transformation', 'This connection highlights the transformation that occurs through spiritual rebirth. Both passages emphasize the transition from the old nature to a new creation in the Spirit.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 6, 46, 15, 47, 50, 'that which is born of the flesh is flesh', 'Connection of Flesh and Spirit', 'Both passages emphasize the distinction between the earthly and the heavenly. John 3:6 speaks of the nature of flesh and spirit, while 1 Corinthians 15:47-50 contrasts the earthy man with the heavenly man, highlighting the inability of flesh to inherit the kingdom of God.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 6, 45, 7, 18, 18, 'that which is born of the flesh is flesh', 'Connection of Flesh and Spirit', 'Both passages emphasize the distinction between flesh and spirit. John 3:6 states that ''that which is born of the flesh is flesh,'' while Romans 7:18 reflects on the lack of good in the flesh, highlighting the struggle between these two natures.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 6, 46, 6, 17, 17, 'that which is born of the Spirit', 'Connection of Spirit and Unity', 'Both passages emphasize the relationship between the Spirit and unity with the Lord. John 3:6 speaks of being born of the Spirit, while 1 Corinthians 6:17 highlights being one spirit with the Lord.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 7, 43, 3, 3, 3, 'Ye must be born again', 'Connection on Being Born Again', 'Both passages emphasize the necessity of being ''born again'' to access spiritual truths. This connection highlights the importance of spiritual rebirth in understanding the kingdom of God.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 7, 49, 4, 22, 24, 'Ye must be born again', 'New Birth and Renewal', 'Both passages emphasize the necessity of transformation. John 3:7 speaks of being ''born again,'' while Ephesians 4:22-24 discusses putting off the ''old man'' and putting on the ''new man,'' highlighting a similar theme of spiritual renewal.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 7, 45, 12, 1, 2, 'Ye must be born again', 'Transformation and New Birth', 'This connection highlights the theme of transformation in both passages. John 3:7 speaks of being ''born again,'' while Romans 12:2 emphasizes being ''transformed by the renewing of your mind.'' Both suggest a fundamental change in one''s spiritual state.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 7, 43, 3, 12, 12, 'Ye must be born again', 'Connection of Belief and Understanding', 'This connection highlights the necessity of belief in understanding spiritual truths. Both passages emphasize the challenge of accepting deeper, heavenly concepts when earthly matters are not believed.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 7, 60, 1, 22, 22, 'Ye must be born again', 'Connection of Spiritual Renewal', 'This connection highlights the theme of spiritual transformation. Both passages emphasize the necessity of a change in the believer''s heart, with John 3:7 stating the need to be ''born again'' and 1 Peter 1:22 focusing on ''purified your souls'' through obedience.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 7, 66, 21, 27, 27, 'Ye must be born again', 'Connection of New Birth and Life', 'This connection highlights the necessity of being ''born again'' to be among those ''written in the Lamb’s book of life.'' Both passages emphasize the transformation required for entry into eternal life.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 7, 40, 13, 33, 35, 'Ye must be born again', 'Transformation and the Kingdom', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of transformation. John 3:7 speaks of being ''born again,'' while Matthew 13:33 illustrates the transformative nature of the kingdom of heaven through leaven.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 8, 21, 11, 4, 5, 'the spirit', 'Connection of Spirit and Understanding', 'This connection highlights the mysterious nature of the Spirit in both passages. John 3:8 speaks of the Spirit''s unpredictability, while Ecclesiastes 11:5 emphasizes our ignorance of the Spirit''s workings.', 'theme', 0.573, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 8, 46, 2, 11, 11, 'born of the Spirit', 'Connection of Spirit Understanding', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the Spirit in understanding and experiencing the divine. John 3:8 describes the mysterious nature of those born of the Spirit, while 1 Corinthians 2:11 highlights that only the Spirit of God knows the things of God.', 'theme', 0.489, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 8, 44, 2, 2, 2, 'the wind bloweth where it listeth', 'Connection of Wind Imagery', 'This connection highlights the imagery of wind in both passages. John 3:8 describes the Spirit''s movement like the wind, while Acts 2:2 depicts a sound of a rushing mighty wind, symbolizing the arrival of the Holy Spirit.', 'theme', 0.45399999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 8, 26, 37, 9, 9, 'the wind', 'Connection of Wind and Spirit', 'This connection highlights the theme of the wind as a symbol of the Spirit''s movement and life-giving power. Both passages emphasize the mysterious nature of the wind and its role in bringing life, as seen in the context of spiritual rebirth and resurrection.', 'theme', 0.43999999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 8, 62, 2, 29, 29, 'born of the Spirit', 'Connection of Righteousness and Spirit', 'This connection highlights the theme of being ''born'' from a divine source. Both passages emphasize that those who are born of the Spirit or of Him exhibit righteousness in their actions.', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 8, 41, 4, 26, 29, 'the wind bloweth where it listeth', 'Connection of Growth and Mystery', 'This connection highlights the mysterious nature of spiritual growth and the kingdom of God. Both passages emphasize processes that occur beyond human understanding, with the wind and seed representing unseen forces at work.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 8, 44, 4, 31, 31, 'born of the Spirit', 'Connection of the Spirit''s Movement', 'Both passages emphasize the dynamic and powerful nature of the Holy Spirit. In John 3:8, the Spirit''s movement is likened to the wind, while Acts 4:31 describes a physical manifestation of that power as the place was shaken.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 9, 43, 6, 60, 60, 'How can these things be?', 'Difficulty in Understanding Teachings', 'This connection highlights the struggle of individuals to comprehend profound spiritual truths. Both Nicodemus and the disciples express confusion and difficulty in understanding Jesus'' teachings.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 9, 23, 42, 16, 16, 'How can these things be?', 'Blindness and Understanding', 'This connection highlights the theme of spiritual blindness and the quest for understanding. Nicodemus''s question, ''How can these things be?'' reflects a lack of comprehension, while Isaiah speaks of leading the blind in unfamiliar paths, suggesting divine guidance towards enlightenment.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 9, 42, 1, 34, 34, 'How can these things be?', 'Questions of Understanding', 'Both passages emphasize a question of understanding regarding miraculous events. Nicodemus and Mary both express confusion about how these extraordinary occurrences can happen.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 9, 43, 6, 52, 52, 'How can these things be?', 'Questions of Understanding', 'Both passages emphasize a struggle to comprehend Jesus'' teachings. Nicodemus questions how spiritual rebirth is possible, while the Jews question how Jesus can provide his flesh to eat.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 9, 20, 4, 18, 18, 'How can these things be?', 'Path of Understanding and Light', 'This connection highlights the journey of understanding spiritual truths. Nicodemus''s question reflects a search for clarity, while Proverbs describes the just''s path as increasingly illuminated.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 9, 41, 8, 24, 25, 'How can these things be?', 'Understanding Spiritual Insight', 'This connection highlights the theme of gradual understanding. In John 3:9, Nicodemus struggles to comprehend spiritual truths, while in Mark 8:24-25, the blind man experiences a progressive restoration of sight, symbolizing the journey toward clarity in perception.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 10, 40, 22, 29, 29, 'knowest not these things', 'Knowledge of Scriptures and God', 'This connection highlights the theme of understanding scripture and divine power. Both passages emphasize the failure of religious leaders to grasp essential truths about God and His word.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 10, 24, 8, 8, 9, 'knowest not these things', 'Wisdom and Knowledge Rejection', 'This connection highlights the theme of wisdom and knowledge among the leaders of Israel. Both passages emphasize the failure of the wise to recognize and accept the truth of God''s word.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 10, 26, 11, 19, 19, NULL, 'Transformation of the Heart', 'This connection highlights the theme of spiritual renewal. In John 3:10, Jesus addresses the need for understanding spiritual truths, while Ezekiel 11:19 speaks of giving a new heart, indicating a transformation necessary for true comprehension.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
