VALUES
(43, 3, 14, 12, 18, 4, 4, 'lifted up the serpent', 'Connection of Serpent Imagery', 'This connection highlights the theme of the serpent as a symbol of salvation and judgment. In John 3:14, the lifting up of the serpent parallels the lifting up of the Son of man, while 2 Kings 18:4 discusses the destruction of the brasen serpent, indicating a shift in its significance.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 14, 19, 22, 16, 16, 'lifted up', 'Connection of Suffering and Salvation', 'This connection highlights the theme of being ''lifted up'' and the suffering involved in salvation. Both passages emphasize the physical suffering of the Son of man and the piercing referenced in Psalms.', 'theme', 0.391, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 15, 43, 3, 16, 16, 'whosoever believeth in him should not perish', 'Connection of Belief and Eternal Life', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of belief in Jesus for attaining eternal life. They share the phrase ''whosoever believeth in him should not perish'' to highlight this central theme.', 'theme', 0.43299999999999994, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 15, 43, 6, 40, 40, 'believeth in him should not perish', 'Connection of Eternal Life', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of believing in the Son to attain eternal life. They highlight the promise of everlasting life for those who believe, linking faith in Jesus with salvation.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 15, 62, 5, 11, 13, 'eternal life', 'Eternal Life Through Belief', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of eternal life granted through belief in the Son of God. John 3:15 states that believers will not perish but have eternal life, while 1 John 5:11-13 affirms that this life is in the Son and assures believers of their eternal life.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 15, 58, 7, 25, 25, 'eternal life', 'Salvation and Eternal Life', 'This connection highlights the theme of salvation in both passages. John 3:15 emphasizes eternal life for believers, while Hebrews 7:25 speaks of saving those who come to God through Christ.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 15, 62, 5, 1, 1, 'whosoever believeth', 'Connection of Belief and Life', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of belief in Jesus for spiritual life. John 3:15 speaks of eternal life through belief, while 1 John 5:1 connects belief in Jesus as the Christ to being born of God.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 15, 23, 45, 22, 22, NULL, 'Salvation for All Believers', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of salvation available to all. John 3:15 speaks of belief leading to eternal life, while Isaiah 45:22 calls for all to look to God for salvation.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 15, 45, 10, 9, 14, 'whosoever believeth', 'Connection of Belief and Salvation', 'Both passages emphasize belief in Jesus as essential for salvation. They highlight that ''whosoever believeth'' will not perish and will be saved, reinforcing the universal call to faith.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 16, 1, 22, 12, 12, NULL, 'Connection of Sacrifice and Love', 'This connection highlights the theme of sacrificial love, as both passages refer to an ''only son.'' In Genesis, the willingness to sacrifice Isaac demonstrates profound faith, while John emphasizes God''s love in giving His only Son for humanity''s salvation.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 16, 40, 9, 13, 13, 'whosoever believeth in him', 'God''s Mercy and Salvation', 'This connection highlights God''s desire for mercy and the call for sinners to repentance, which aligns with the theme of salvation in John 3:16. Both passages emphasize God''s love and the offer of everlasting life to those who believe.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 16, 41, 12, 6, 6, 'only begotten Son', 'Connection of God''s Son', 'Both passages emphasize the sending of God''s son. John 3:16 highlights the love of God in giving His only begotten Son, while Mark 12:6 refers to the son as ''his wellbeloved'' sent to be reverenced.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 16, 42, 2, 14, 14, NULL, 'Connection of Divine Love and Peace', 'Both passages emphasize God''s goodwill toward humanity. John 3:16 speaks of God''s love through the gift of His Son, while Luke 2:14 proclaims peace and goodwill on earth, reflecting the outcome of that divine love.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 16, 43, 1, 14, 14, 'only begotten Son', 'Connection of God''s Love and Incarnation', 'This connection highlights the theme of God''s love through the giving of His Son, as seen in both passages. John 3:16 emphasizes the gift of the ''only begotten Son,'' while John 1:14 describes the incarnation of ''the Word'' as ''the only begotten of the Father.''', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 16, 43, 1, 29, 29, 'the world', 'God''s Love and Sin Removal', 'Both passages emphasize God''s action towards the world. John 3:16 highlights God''s love in giving His Son, while John 1:29 identifies Jesus as the Lamb who takes away sin, linking His sacrificial role to God''s love for humanity.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 16, 45, 5, 8, 8, 'God so loved the world', 'God''s Love and Sacrifice', 'Both passages emphasize God''s love and the sacrificial death of Christ. John 3:16 highlights God''s love through the giving of His Son, while Romans 5:8 illustrates that love by stating Christ died for sinners.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 17, 42, 19, 10, 10, 'might be saved', 'Salvation Focus in Both Passages', 'Both passages emphasize the purpose of Jesus'' mission to save the lost. John 3:17 highlights that the world might be saved through Him, while Luke 19:10 states He came to seek and to save that which was lost.', 'theme', 0.727, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 17, 62, 4, 14, 14, 'the world through him might be saved', 'Connection of Salvation Theme', 'Both passages emphasize that God sent his Son to save the world. This connection highlights the purpose of Jesus'' mission as a savior rather than a condemner.', 'theme', 0.727, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 17, 43, 12, 47, 48, NULL, 'Connection of Salvation and Judgment', 'Both passages emphasize that Jesus was sent not to condemn but to save the world. They highlight the distinction between His mission of salvation and the eventual judgment that comes from rejecting His words.', 'theme', 0.629, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 17, 43, 6, 57, 57, 'sent not his Son into the world', 'Connection of Divine Sending', 'This connection highlights the theme of God sending His Son for the purpose of life and salvation. Both passages emphasize the relationship between the Father and the Son, indicating that through Jesus, believers can attain eternal life.', 'theme', 0.5309999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 17, 54, 2, 5, 6, 'that the world through him might be saved', 'Salvation through Christ''s Mediation', 'Both passages emphasize the role of Christ in salvation. John 3:17 highlights that the world might be saved through Him, while 1 Timothy 2:5-6 identifies Christ as the mediator who gave Himself as a ransom for all.', 'theme', 0.489, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 17, 62, 2, 2, 2, 'the world through him might be saved', 'Salvation for the Whole World', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of salvation offered through Jesus. John 3:17 highlights that the purpose of Jesus'' coming was to save the world, while 1 John 2:2 states that he is the propitiation for the sins of the whole world.', 'theme', 0.44699999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 17, 38, 9, 9, 9, NULL, 'Connection of Salvation and Kingship', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of salvation. John 3:17 states that the world might be saved through the Son, while Zechariah 9:9 speaks of a King who brings salvation.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 18, 41, 16, 16, 16, 'he that believeth not is condemned already', 'Belief and Condemnation Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the consequences of belief and unbelief. John 3:18 states that those who believe are not condemned, while Mark 16:16 indicates that those who believe not shall be damned.', 'theme', 0.503, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 18, 62, 5, 10, 10, 'believeth not', 'Belief and Condemnation Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the consequences of belief in the Son of God. John 3:18 states that those who believe are not condemned, while 1 John 5:10 highlights that disbelief makes one a liar, reflecting the serious implications of rejecting God''s record of His Son.', 'theme', 0.503, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 18, 45, 8, 1, 1, 'condemned already, because he hath not believed', 'Condemnation and Belief in Christ', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of condemnation related to belief in Christ. John 3:18 states that those who do not believe are condemned, while Romans 8:1 assures that there is no condemnation for those in Christ Jesus.', 'theme', 0.475, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 18, 43, 5, 24, 24, 'not condemned', 'Condemnation and Belief Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the consequences of belief and condemnation. John 3:18 states that those who believe are not condemned, while John 5:24 reinforces that believers shall not come into condemnation.', 'theme', 0.45399999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 18, 43, 3, 36, 36, 'believeth not', 'Connection of Belief and Condemnation', 'Both passages emphasize the consequences of belief in the Son. The first verse states that those who believe are not condemned, while the second reinforces that belief leads to everlasting life, contrasting with the condemnation for disbelief.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 18, 45, 5, 1, 1, 'believeth not', 'Faith and Justification Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of belief in Jesus for salvation. John 3:18 discusses condemnation for unbelief, while Romans 5:1 highlights justification by faith, leading to peace with God.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 18, 62, 4, 9, 9, 'only begotten Son of God', 'Connection of Belief and Life', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of belief in the only begotten Son of God. John 3:18 discusses condemnation for unbelief, while 1 John 4:9 highlights the purpose of His coming for our life.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
