(43, 3, 23, 9, 9, 4, 4, 'Salim', 'Connection of Locations', 'Both passages mention locations named Salim and Shalim, highlighting the geographical significance in their narratives. This connection emphasizes the importance of place in the context of the events described.', 'keyword', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 23, 24, 51, 13, 13, 'much water', 'Connection of Water Imagery', 'This connection highlights the significance of water in both passages. John 3:23 mentions ''much water'' for baptism, while Jeremiah 51:13 refers to ''many waters'' in a context of judgment.', 'theme', 0.314, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 24, 40, 4, 12, 12, 'John was not yet cast into prison', 'John''s Imprisonment and Jesus'' Ministry', 'This connection highlights the timeline of events regarding John the Baptist''s imprisonment. The first passage notes that John was not yet cast into prison, while the second indicates that Jesus began his ministry after John''s imprisonment.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 24, 40, 14, 3, 3, 'John was not yet cast into prison', 'Connection of John the Baptist''s Imprisonment', 'This connection highlights the timeline of John the Baptist''s ministry. John 3:24 notes that he was not yet imprisoned, while Matthew 14:3 describes the event of his imprisonment.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 24, 41, 6, 17, 17, 'For John was not yet cast into prison.', 'John''s Imprisonment Timeline', 'This connection highlights the timeline of John the Baptist''s imprisonment. John 3:24 indicates that he was not yet imprisoned, while Mark 6:17 describes the event of his imprisonment by Herod.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 24, 42, 3, 19, 20, 'For John was not yet cast into prison.', 'Connection of John''s Imprisonment', 'This connection highlights the timeline of John the Baptist''s ministry, as indicated in John 3:24, where it notes he was not yet imprisoned. Luke 3:19-20 details the events leading to his imprisonment, emphasizing the significance of his prophetic role before being shut up by Herod.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 24, 42, 9, 7, 9, 'John was not yet cast into prison', 'Connection Between John and Herod', 'This connection highlights the presence of John before his imprisonment and Herod''s subsequent confusion about his fate. Both passages emphasize John''s significance in the narrative, as Herod reflects on John''s beheading while hearing rumors of his return.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 25, 43, 2, 6, 6, NULL, 'Purification Practices in John', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of purification, with John 3:25 discussing a question about purifying and John 2:6 mentioning waterpots used for the purifying of the Jews. This connection highlights the significance of purification rituals in the context of John''s ministry.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 25, 40, 3, 11, 11, 'purifying', 'Baptism and Purification Themes', 'This connection highlights the theme of purification through baptism. Both passages discuss the act of baptism, with John emphasizing water for repentance and the one to come offering a more profound spiritual baptism.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 25, 58, 6, 2, 2, 'purifying', 'Connection of Purification and Baptism', 'This connection highlights the theme of purification through baptism. Both passages emphasize the significance of ritual practices related to spiritual cleansing and renewal.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 25, 58, 9, 10, 10, 'purifying', 'Purification and Washings Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of purification practices in both passages. John 3:25 mentions a question about ''purifying,'' while Hebrews 9:10 refers to ''divers washings,'' indicating a shared focus on ritualistic cleansing.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 25, 60, 3, 21, 21, 'purifying', 'Connection of Purification and Baptism', 'This connection highlights the theme of purification in both passages. John 3:25 discusses ''purifying,'' while 1 Peter 3:21 emphasizes baptism as a means of spiritual cleansing.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 25, 41, 7, 2, 5, 'purifying', 'Purification and Tradition', 'This connection highlights the theme of purification practices in both passages. John 3:25 discusses a question about purifying, while Mark 7:2-5 addresses the tradition of washing hands before eating, emphasizing the importance of ritual cleanliness.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 25, 41, 7, 8, 8, 'purifying', 'Tradition of Purification Practices', 'This connection highlights the theme of purification practices in both passages. John 3:25 discusses a question about purifying, while Mark 7:8 critiques the tradition of washing, indicating a focus on ritual cleanliness.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 26, 43, 1, 7, 7, NULL, 'Witness and Belief Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the role of a witness. John 3:26 refers to John the Baptist bearing witness to Jesus, while John 1:7 highlights the purpose of that witness for belief.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 26, 43, 1, 15, 15, NULL, 'Witness of John the Baptist', 'Both passages emphasize John''s role as a witness to Jesus. In John 3:26, John''s followers note that many are coming to Jesus, while John 1:15 highlights John''s declaration that Jesus is preferred before him.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 26, 59, 3, 14, 18, 'all men come to him', 'Wisdom and Strife Connection', 'This connection highlights the contrast between the ''envying and strife'' mentioned in James and the communal response to Jesus'' baptism in John. Both passages emphasize the importance of purity and peace over division and competition.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 26, 23, 45, 23, 23, 'all men come to him', 'Bowing and Witnessing Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of recognition and submission to authority. In John 3:26, people acknowledge Jesus'' growing influence, while Isaiah 45:23 emphasizes that every knee will bow, indicating ultimate recognition of God''s authority.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 26, 44, 19, 26, 27, 'all men come to him', 'Influence of Preachers on Followers', 'This connection highlights the theme of influential figures drawing followers to themselves. In John, Jesus is gaining followers, while in Acts, Paul is persuading many away from idol worship.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 26, 46, 3, 3, 5, 'all men come to him', 'Carnality and Division in Ministry', 'This connection highlights the theme of division among followers in both passages. John 3:26 mentions people coming to Jesus, while 1 Corinthians 3:3-5 addresses divisions among those claiming allegiance to different leaders.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 26, 48, 5, 20, 21, 'all men come to him', 'Conflict Over Authority', 'This connection highlights the theme of rivalry and competition for followers. In John 3:26, the mention of ''all men come to him'' suggests a shift in allegiance, while Galatians 5:20-21 lists behaviors like ''strife'' and ''envyings'' that can arise from such competition.', 'theme', 0.321, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 27, 59, 1, 17, 17, 'except it be given him from heaven', 'Gifts from Above', 'Both passages emphasize that gifts come from above, highlighting the divine source of all good things. John 3:27 states that nothing can be received unless given from heaven, while James 1:17 affirms that every good gift is from the Father.', 'theme', 0.538, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 27, 46, 4, 7, 7, 'except it be given him from heaven', 'Receiving from God', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of receiving gifts from God. John 3:27 states that nothing can be received except from heaven, while 1 Corinthians 4:7 questions what one has that was not received, highlighting the same theme of divine provision.', 'theme', 0.46799999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 27, 46, 15, 10, 10, 'except it be given him from heaven', 'Grace and Divine Provision', 'This connection highlights the theme of grace as a divine gift. Both passages emphasize that what one receives or achieves is ultimately given by God, whether through grace or heavenly provision.', 'theme', 0.426, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 27, 60, 4, 10, 11, 'except it be given him from heaven', 'Divine Gifts and Stewardship', 'This connection highlights the theme of receiving gifts from God and the responsibility to use them. Both passages emphasize that what one receives is from God, and believers are called to minister these gifts to others.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 27, 30, 7, 15, 15, 'except it be given him from heaven', 'Divine Authority in Calling', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine authority in both passages. John emphasizes that a man can receive nothing unless it is given from heaven, while Amos illustrates his prophetic calling as initiated by the Lord.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 27, 4, 17, 5, 5, 'except it be given him from heaven', 'Divine Authority and Selection', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine selection in both passages. John 3:27 emphasizes that authority and gifts come from heaven, while Numbers 17:5 illustrates God''s choice of a rod to end dissent, showcasing His control over leadership.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 27, 24, 1, 5, 5, 'except it be given him from heaven', 'Divine Knowledge and Ordination', 'This connection highlights the theme of divine knowledge and ordination. Both passages emphasize that God''s involvement precedes human existence and purpose.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 28, 43, 1, 20, 20, 'I am not the Christ', 'John''s Confession of Identity', 'Both passages emphasize John''s declaration that he is not the Christ. This connection highlights his role as a forerunner to Jesus, reinforcing his humility and purpose.', 'theme', 0.363, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 28, 40, 3, 11, 12, 'I am not the Christ', 'John''s Role Before Christ', 'Both passages emphasize John''s role as a forerunner to Christ. John explicitly states he is not the Christ, while also highlighting the superiority of the one who comes after him.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
