(43, 3, 32, 45, 10, 16, 21, 'no man receiveth his testimony', 'Testimony and Obedience Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of testimony and belief. John 3:32 mentions the lack of reception of testimony, while Romans 10:16 addresses disobedience to the gospel despite hearing it.', 'theme', 0.3, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 32, 45, 11, 2, 6, 'no man receiveth his testimony', 'Testimony and Remnant Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of testimony and reception. In John, the lack of acceptance of testimony parallels the remnant in Romans, who remain faithful despite widespread rejection. Both passages emphasize the idea of a select group acknowledging truth amidst disbelief.', 'theme', 0.3, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 33, 49, 1, 13, 13, 'set to his seal that God is true', 'Sealing and Truth Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of being sealed as a sign of truth. Both passages emphasize the act of receiving testimony and believing, which leads to being sealed, affirming God''s truth.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 33, 58, 6, 17, 17, 'God is true', 'God''s Truth and Immutability', 'This connection highlights the theme of God''s truthfulness and reliability. Both passages emphasize the assurance that God is true and that His promises are immutable, as confirmed by His oath.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 33, 47, 1, 18, 18, 'God is true', 'Truthfulness of God', 'Both passages emphasize the truthfulness of God. John 3:33 states that God is true, while 2 Corinthians 1:18 affirms this truth in relation to the speaker''s message.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 33, 56, 1, 1, 2, 'God is true', 'Truth and God''s Promises', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of truth, with John affirming that God is true and Titus highlighting the acknowledgment of truth that leads to godliness. Additionally, Titus mentions God''s promise of eternal life, reinforcing the reliability of God''s word, which aligns with the affirmation of truth in John.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 33, 43, 6, 27, 27, 'God is true', 'Connection of Sealing and Testimony', 'This connection highlights the theme of God''s truth and the sealing of His chosen. Both passages emphasize the importance of receiving God''s testimony and the sealing of the Son of man by God.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 33, 45, 3, 3, 4, 'God is true', 'Truth and Belief Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of God''s truthfulness in contrast to human unbelief. John 3:33 asserts that those who accept God''s testimony affirm His truth, while Romans 3:4 states that God is true despite human doubt.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 33, 45, 4, 18, 21, 'God is true', 'Faith and God''s Promises', 'This connection highlights the theme of belief in God''s truth and promises. Both passages emphasize the importance of faith in God''s ability to fulfill His word, as seen in the assurance of God''s truth in John and Abraham''s unwavering faith in Romans.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 34, 44, 10, 38, 38, 'for God giveth not the Spirit by measure unto him', 'Connection of Divine Anointing', 'Both passages emphasize the role of the Holy Spirit in Jesus'' ministry. John 3:34 states that God gives the Spirit without measure to Jesus, while Acts 10:38 describes His anointing with the Holy Ghost and power.', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 34, 40, 12, 18, 18, 'God giveth not the Spirit by measure', 'Connection of Divine Spirit', 'Both passages emphasize the giving of God''s Spirit. John 3:34 states that God gives the Spirit without measure, while Matthew 12:18 mentions putting the Spirit upon His chosen servant.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 34, 43, 15, 26, 26, 'God giveth not the Spirit by measure', 'Connection of the Spirit''s Role', 'This connection highlights the role of the Spirit in both passages. John 3:34 emphasizes that God gives the Spirit without measure to the one He sends, while John 15:26 describes the Spirit of truth sent from the Father to testify of Jesus.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
