(43, 3, 35, 43, 17, 2, 2, 'given all things into his hand', 'Authority of the Son', 'Both passages emphasize the authority given to the Son. In John 3:35, it states that the Father has given all things into his hand, while John 17:2 highlights that he has power over all flesh.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(43, 3, 35, 19, 2, 8, 8, 'given all things into his hand', 'Inheritance and Authority Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of inheritance and authority given by God. In John 3:35, the Father gives all things into the Son''s hand, while Psalms 2:8 speaks of God granting the heathen as an inheritance to the Son.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
